Peruvian anchoveta

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peruvian_anchoveta

  • Max length 8 inches
  • Live 3 years
  • Sensitive to environmental conditions (El Niño)

Fishery

Photo credit: Angencia Andina

  • “The most heavily exploited fish in world history”
  • Mostly used for fish meal and oil
  • Small human consumption market
  • Evidence of a crash in early 2015

Data

Survey observations for 2001 and 2003

  • Zero-inflated continuous (biomass)
  • Different distribution and abundance by years
  • Aggregate by taking mean within each triangle
  • Not clear why this was necessary (use projection matrix!)
  • Am I missing something???

Need to account for the zeros

Use two latent Gaussian fields with linear predictors

\[\begin{aligned} \eta^{(1)}(s_i, t) &= \vec{Z}^{(1)}(s_i,t)\vec{\beta}^{(1)} + f^{(1)}(t) + f_s^{(1)}(s_i, t) + f_{st}^{(1)}(s_i,t)\\ \eta^{(2)}(s_i, t) &= \vec{Z}^{(2)}(s_i,t)\vec{\beta}^{(2)} + f^{(2)}(t) + f_s^{(2)}(s_i, t) + f_{st}^{(2)}(s_i,t) \end{aligned}\]

And a delta-gamma density

\[\begin{aligned} y(s_i,t) = 0 &\sim \operatorname{Bernoulli}\left(\operatorname{logit}^{-1}\left(\eta^{(1)}(s_i,t)\right)\right)\\ y(s_i,t) \mid y(s_i,t) > 0 &\sim \operatorname{Gamma}\left(\phi, \frac{\phi}{\exp\left(\eta^{(2)}(s_i,t)\right)}\right) \end{aligned}\]

  • Important!
  • Other common options: delta-log Normal
  • Jim’s Poisson link
  • ɸ is a dispersion parameter

Covariates

In all models:

  • CD: Distance to coast
  • Depth
  • SST: Sea surface temperature

In absence/presence component:

  • Quadratic effect of latitude

In the S3 & ST3 models:

  • 3-year periodic components; \(\sin(2\pi t / 3)\) and \(\cos(2 \pi t / 3)\);
  • These are in Z
  • Not clear if CV and depth confounded
  • 3-year cycle estimated from periodogram
  • Could they have used something like Pacific Decadal Oscillation (instead of SST or 3-year periodic)?
  • More flexible than fixed 3-year cycle?

Temporal effects

Models S2 and ST2, AR(1):

\[\begin{aligned} f(1) &\sim \operatorname{Normal}\left(0, \frac{1}{\tau_{ar}\left(1 - b^{2}\right)}\right)\\ f(t) &= b \cdot f(t-1) + \epsilon_{ar}(t)\\ \epsilon_{ar}(t) &\sim \operatorname{Normal}\left(0, \frac{1}{\tau_{ar}}\right) \quad t = 2,\dots,T \end{aligned}\]

  • For simplicity, dropped (k) and tildes

Temporal effects

Models S4 and ST4, RW(2):

\[\begin{aligned} f(t) &= 2 \cdot f(t + 1) - f(t + 2) + \epsilon_{rw2}(t)\\ \epsilon_{rw2}(t) &\sim \operatorname{Normal}\left(0, \frac{1}{\tau_{rw2}}\right) \quad t = 1,\dots,T-2 \end{aligned}\]

  • They note that this is similar to a penalized spline
  • Not clear how the final two time steps are modeled

Spatial effects

A GRF

\[\vec{f}_s(\cdot,t) \stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim} \operatorname{MVN}\left(\vec{0}, \vec{Q}_s^{-1}\right) \quad t = 1,\dots,T\]

where \(\vec{Q}_s\) is associated with the solution to

\[\left( \kappa^2 - \Delta \right)^{\alpha / 2}(\tau X(s)) = G(s), \quad s \in \mathbb{R}^n\]

through its weak solution \[\left[ \langle \phi_i,(\kappa^2 - \Delta)^{\alpha/2} \tilde{X}\rangle_\Omega\right] \stackrel{D}{=} \left[\langle \phi_i,G\rangle\right]\]

approximating a Matérn covariance with \(\nu = 1\).

SPDE Mesh

Fig. 2, 1147 nodes

  • Dashed line is area of interest
  • Did they leave enough room for edge effects?

Spatiotemporal effects

An AR(1) process on the GRF

\[\begin{aligned} \vec{f}_{st}(\cdot, 1) &\sim \operatorname{MVN}\left(\vec{0}, \frac{1}{\left(1 - a^{2}\right)}\vec{Q}_w^{-1}\right)\\ \vec{f}_{st}(\cdot,t) &= a \cdot \vec{f}_{st}(\cdot,t - 1) + \vec{w}(\cdot, t)\\ \vec{w}(\cdot, t) &\stackrel{\text{iid}}{\sim} \operatorname{MVN}\left(\vec{0}, \vec{Q}_w^{-1}\right) \quad t = 2,\dots,T \end{aligned}\]

  • So start with a Matérn GRF
  • Then it changes as an AR1 with MVN innovations

  • 9 models were fit
  • S· are spatial
  • ST· are spatiotemporal (AR1 on spatial effects)
  • S-ST includes both
  • ·2 include AR(1) on overall mean
  • ·3 include 3-year periodic terms (sin and cos) in covariates
  • ·4 include RW(2) on overall mean

Covariates on absence

Generally: - ↑ distance to coast → ↓ presence - Extreme latitudes → ↓ presence - ↑ depth → ↓ presence - ↑ SST → ↓ presence - El Niño → ↑ SST in some areas

Covariates on abundance

  • ↑ depth → ↓ abundance
  • ↑ SST → ↑ abundance, but must be in tolerable range (nonlinear relationship likely here)

  • S2 for cheap predictions (AR1 time with independent spatial processes)
  • Authors choose ST1 for further work, balancing computation time, estimation, and prediction
  • S-ST also performs well, but costly to fit
